This paper discusses the use of Hierarchical Task Network (HTN) planning, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that deals with planning and decision-making. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the extension of the JSHOP2 planner, which is a domain-independent planning system, indicating that it falls under the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper's focus on home and building automation environments suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the planner, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
